1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,931
Kafka guarantees total ordering within a single partition.

2
00:00:04,881 --> 00:00:12,894
A consumer reading partition P will receive records in the exact order they were appended by the producer.

3
00:00:12,894 --> 00:00:17,000
there's no ordering guarantee across partitions.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:23,513
This one concept shows up in literally every system design interview at FAANG.

5
00:00:23,513 --> 00:00:27,921
Everyone says Custom Partitioner is the best approach.

6
00:00:27,921 --> 00:00:32,526
That is , actually wrong for most real-world systems.

7
00:00:32,526 --> 00:00:35,552
I will show you why in a moment.

